Wil jij je graag ontwikkelen tot een Financial Controller? Combineer jij jouw analytische en consultatieve vaardigheden met accounting skills, boekhoudkundige ervaring en controlling taken? Dan is deze brede finance functie echt iets voor jou!
DE FUNCTIE
Enreach zoekt een teamspeler die zich energiek voelt bij een functie waarbij je echt een verschil kan maken. Je taken omvatten onder andere het maken van financiële analyses en rapportages, die je graag deelt met je collega's.
DE FUNCTIE
Als Financial Controller richt jij je op het optimaliseren van financiële processen en workflows en draag je actief bij aan de “Planning & Control” cyclus. Je helpt diverse teams met het verkrijgen van inzicht over kostenstromen en werkt mee aan mogelijke verbeteringen ten aanzien van financiële procedures, analyses en rapportages. Jij bent onderdeel van het Finance/Business control team.
Belangrijke werkzaamheden zijn:
Consolideren en rapporteren van de maandelijkse resultaten;
Opmaken en beheren en verbeteren van financiële rapportages, met name gericht op de kosten;
Uitvoeren van financiële analyses en werken aan verbetertrajecten;
Bijdragen aan de planning en budgetcyclus;
Je ondersteunt het team van GL-Accountants met rapportages en analyses;
Je assisteert bij het beantwoorden van vragen van business control;
Je voert een aantal maandelijkse analyses uit op kostendrivers inclusief payroll;
Je geeft actief inzicht en werkt samen met verschillende afdelingen;
Je biedt ondersteuning bij het signaleren en verklaren van verschillen tussen actuals en budgetten .
WIE BEN JIJ?
Jouw communicatieve vaardigheden in het Nederlands en Engels zijn sterk ontwikkeld. Je bent zelfverzekerd en daadkrachtig en straalt een natuurlijk vertrouwen uit. Je pakt nieuwe werkzaamheden snel op en je wilt graag verder groeien tot een breed ontwikkelde finance professional. Je hebt oog voor detail en werkt nauwkeurig
Verder heb je:
Minimaal een afgeronde HBO opleiding richting Bedrijfseconomie, F&C, SPD etc.;
Minimaal 2 jaar werkervaring in een financiële functie;
Goed ontwikkelde analytische en consultatieve vaardigheden;
Ruime ervaring met het opstellen van financiële rapportages;
Gevorderde kennis van MS Excel;
Kennis van payroll is een pré.
WAT BIEDEN WIJ?
Een innovatieve en ondernemende omgeving die altijd in beweging is en verandert;
We ‘work hard / play hard’ en we houden van een informele en gezellige manier van omgaan met elkaar;
De mogelijkheid om te werken in een non-hierarchische, internationale omgeving met ruime mogelijkheden voor persoonlijke ontwikkeling en professionele ontwikkeling;
En natuurlijk een goed salaris en secundaire arbeidsvoorwaarden;
Flexibele werktijden en thuis werken is bespreekbaar;
Er is een uitstekende pensioenregeling;
Bijdrage in reiskosten en thuiswerken;
Je krijgt een laptop en telefoon van de zaak.
WIJ ZIJN ENREACH
Enreach is een marktleider op het gebied van communicatie. Wij bieden het meest stabiele en innovatieve communicatieplatform voor de commerciële markt. Via ons eigen netwerk (met ondersteuning van verschillende onderling verbonden datacenters) leveren wij professionele mobiele, telefonie- en datadiensten met behulp van vooruitstrevende ICT-technieken. Door onze flexibele en professionele aanpak hebben we een belangrijke marktpositie verworven die we de komende jaren verder willen uitbouwen via het indirecte verkoopkanaal. Je komt te werken in een dynamische organisatie waar geen dag hetzelfde is. In 2017 hebben we ervoor gekozen om onze organisatie te runnen volgens het managementmodel van Holacracy. Wil je hier meer over weten, kijk dan eens op: www.holacracy.com.
INTERESSE?
Solliciteer dan direct hieronder of neem contact op met: Kel van Schie/kel.vanschie@enreach.com of Mara Zondag/mara.zondag@enreach.com.

Your role

Do you have strong numerical skills, are you assertive, committed, and critical, and would you like to work in a young, ambitious and talented team? Then this vacancy might be a good fit for you.

As a (Jr) Financial Controller you will take the lead in the month-end close for the financial control activities, monitor the integrity of the financial figures and are a direct sparring partner for the Financial Controller and the rest of the Finance team. Tasks like monthly reporting, bookkeeping, preparing budgets, analyzing FX matters and participating in the annual audit are appealing and familiar to you. Together with the Finance team you will make sure all financial transactions are processed correctly. Taking initiative, having a strong attention to detail and pro-actively looking for improvements will take the Financial Control team to the next level.

Within the role of (Jr) Financial Controller you will be part of the Financial Control team and report directly to the Financial Controller.

As our new (Jr) Financial Controller you:
execute an adequate and timely month-end close / annual close;
prepare monthly journals for the operational expenses;
take care of the operational expenses analysis;
prepare the monthly reports for the management;
create and maintain accurate reporting of the FX transactions;
ensure compliance with hedge documentation and prepare hedge effectiveness testing for FX forwards;
monitor the foreign currency exposure and our suspense accounts;
support in the preparation of the budget;
participate in the external audit together with the Financial Controller and support in the preparation of the financial statements;
develop, prepare and update internal and external reporting;
follow-up on ad hoc requests from the management or other departments within Interfood;
support the derivatives back-office with the derivatives tasks and (monthly) derivatives accounting;
are the first point of contact for your colleagues in the hubs around the globe and for external stakeholders (CBS, tax authorities, accountants).
pro-actively look for improvements and participate in improvement projects
Your profile

Master’s degree in Accounting or Finance.

1-5 years of relevant working experience in finance/accounting.

Strong numerical skills and experienced in working with Excel.

Good language and communication skills (Dutch and English both verbally and written).

Assertive, committed, independent, proactive, critical, able to deal with deadlines and with a strong attention to detail.

Our offer
Competitive compensation and benefits. Salary depends on your experience and education.
Free delicious and healthy lunch.
Participate in fun team activities.
40 hour work week, 25 holidays, based on a fulltime employment.
We value your personal development and have a strategic focus on our learning program.
Free gym inside our office.
About Interfood

Do you like to work for an international company? Do you value professionality and quality? Are you comfortable in a dynamic environment? But on the other hand looking for cooperation in a close and informal team? Then Interfood is the ideal employer for you.

The Interfood Group is a leading global dairy trading company (milk powders, butter, cheese, dairy blends etc.). The Group consists of 14 offices in all continents with more than 350 employees. Our constant strive for optimal quality, up-to-date knowledge and a profound focus on service, enables Interfood to create the difference for its robust network of both clients and suppliers.

Interfood keeps on growing and developing by its proactive market approach.

We stimulate personal development and initiatives from our employees. Interfood, originally a family-based company, proves that global professionalism can still be combined with a unique personal company culture, in which we focus on following values: Teamwork, Commitment, Continuous Improvement, Professionalism & Responsible Leadership. All contributing to our purpose: Together for better.

Will you become our new team member?

Junior Financial Controller and Reporting Specialist
Who are we?
RNHB is a leading Dutch independent real estate lending business, with in depth knowledge of the Dutch real estate markets. We provide loans for commercial real estate and for residential properties intended for rental or resale. RNHB offers tailor-made debt solutions for the middle segment of the real estate market. We have the strong ambition to expand our business through organic growth and selective portfolio acquisitions to maintain our market leading position as a non-bank lending business. With a solid shareholder base and a good competitive position we have an excellent growth perspective.
What are you going to do?
You will become part of RNHB’s Finance & Control team that is responsible for the financial accounting and reporting of RNHB B.V. and its subsidiaries. RNHB has a complex funding structure that includes private funding transactions and public securitisations using special purpose vehicles. You will play an important role in the monthly closing process (consolidation, financial analysis) and will assist in periodical reporting to the supervisor as well in the preparation of the annual financial statements of both RNHB B.V. as well as of the SPV’s. Assisting in the preparation of quarterly or annual tax filings (both VAT as well as CIT) is also part of the job.
Main tasks & responsibilities
Actively participate in the monthly and annual closing by executing the consolidation and by analysing the correct and complete accounting of transactions in our G/L;
Assist in the preparation of external reporting to supervisors;
Assist in the preparation of consolidated financial statements of RNHB B.V.;
Assist in the preparation of the statutory financial statements of our SPV’s on behalf the trustees;
Monitor qualitative and timely reporting by our external service providers;
Set up financial reports and prepare reconciliations;
Prepare VAT and CIT returns;
Execute and make suggestions for improvement of and improve our processes and controls;
Assist Treasury in performing cash transfers.
What are we looking for?
We are looking for a motivated and smart candidate with several years’ experience in (IFRS) reporting and financial control who enjoys working in a team. To be successful in this position you are someone who is analytical and works accurately. You are willing to learn and are not afraid to ask questions. You have strong communication and interpersonal skills and an intrinsic drive to further improve the organization. And further:
You have completed an education program (Bachelor or Master) in the direction of Business Economics, Accountancy or related;
You have sound knowledge of IFRS and Dutch GAAP;
You have 3 to 5 years of work experience in a similar position;
Preferably you have gained experience in the financial sector;
Knowledge of AFAS or similar accounting system is a plus;
You are not afraid of change and you help us to continuously improve our processes and procedures;
Your English is fluent both in word and writing
What’s in it for you?
Become part of an ambitious team with professional colleagues in an informal company
A modern office next to the station in the heart of Utrecht (WTC)
Modern working conditions, such as unlimited leave and a flexible work from home policy
Freedom to plan and organise your work yourself
Access to GoodHabitz, an online training platform for self-development
A private RNHBar, table tennis and football table
Monthly drinks and events with your colleagues
Real good coffee and fresh fruit every day
A pension scheme
Flexible mobility budget
A personal development budget
Access to sports events and workouts with your colleagues
Do you have questions?
Do you have any questions about the position? Contact our Corporate Recruiter Petra Veurman via pveurman@rnhb.nl. Are you excited about the opportunity and are you the one we are looking for? We are happy to receive your application.

